          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "An 18O beam with an energy of 103.0 MeV. The average",
                "intensity of the 18O beam was about 0.2 pnA, and the",
                "diameter of the beam spot was less than 3 mm.",
                "A Faraday cup was installed about 1.3 m away from the",
                "target to collect the 18O beam dose."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "26-FE-56",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.994
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The thickness of target is",
                "402 ug/cm2."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "26-FE-58",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.963
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The thickness of target is",
                "260 ug/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An array of dE-E silicon detector telescopes",
                "was located downstream of the target to identify the",
                "light ejectile particles."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four HPGe detectors were placed perpendicular",
                "to the beam direction at a distance of about 70 mm",
                "from the target for gamma-ray detection. The absolute",
                "peak efficiency of each HPGe detector was about 0.6%",
                "at 1173.2 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "8-O-16",
                "G"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Each Fe target was irradiated for approximately",
                "2.5 days, and the accumulated number of 16O was",
                "approximately 1.7E5 and 1.3E5 for the 56Fe and 58Fe",
                "targets, respectively. The number of detected",
                "gamma-ray events from 58Fe and 60Fe was about 4.5E3",
                "and 3.4E3, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SURGT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Surrogate technique: The 58Fe(18O,16O) 60Fe",
                "and 56Fe(18O,16O) 58Fe reactions represent",
                "59Fe(n,g)60Fe and 57Fe(n,g)58Fe, respectively.",
                "The gamma intensities 86.0+-2.0% (824 keV) and",
                "66.0+-3.0% (811 keV) were adopted for identification",
                "of 60Fe and 58Fe, respectively.",
                "According to Eq.3 of S.Q.Yan+,J,PR/C,94,015804,2016",
                " (EXFOR 32732),the authors assume the compound",
                "formation cross section is the same for 59Fe+n and",
                "57Fe+n."
              ]
            }
          ],
